322","1321":"1321","1373":"1373","1360":"1360","1371":"1371","Clopton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Clopton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Clopton, Suffolk, England":"Clopton, Suffolk, England","Little, Suffolk,, England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Little Waldingfield, Babergh District, Suffolk, England St Lawrence Churchyard":"Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Wyncoll","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name, toponymic from Winkhill (Lincs), or perhaps topographic from an unattested Middle English * <i>winkel</i>, derived from Old English * <i>wincel</i> ‘nook, corner, bend in a river’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Roger Wyncoll was born in 1321, in Clopton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom as the son of SIR William Wyncoll. He had at least 1 son with Anne Gurdon. He died in 1371, in Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 50, and was buried in Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1321–1371":"1321–1371","1322–1373":"1322–1373","1360–1421":"1360–1421","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1300":"1300","1421":"1421","1322":"1322","1321":"1321","1373":"1373","1360":"1360","1371":"1371","Clopton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Clopton, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Clopton, Suffolk, England":"Clopton, Suffolk, England","Little, Suffolk,, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Little Waldingfield, Babergh District, Suffolk, England St Lawrence Churchyard":"Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1321–1371":"1321–1371","1322–1373":"1322–1373","1360–1421":"1360–1421","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1300":"1300","1421":"1421","1322":"1322","1321":"1321","1373":"1373","1360":"1360","1371":"1371","Clopton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Clopton, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Clopton, Suffolk, England":"Clopton, Suffolk, England","Little, Suffolk,, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Little Waldingfield, Babergh District, Suffolk, England St Lawrence Churchyard":"Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1321–1371":"1321–1371","1322–1373":"1322–1373","1360–1421":"1360–1421","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1300":"1300","1421":"1421","1322":"1322","1321":"1321","1373":"1373","1360":"1360","1371":"1371","Clopton, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Clopton, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Clopton, Suffolk, England":"Clopton, Suffolk, Angleterre","Little, Suffolk,, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Little Waldingfield, Babergh District, Suffolk, England St Lawrence Churchyard":"Little Waldingfield, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Roger Wyncoll est né en 1321, à Clopton, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de SIR William Wyncoll. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Anne Gurdon. Il est décédé en 1371, à Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 50 ans, et a été enter